WEBVTT

00:00.959 --> 00:08.291
♪

00:08.291 --> 00:10.083
LARK: Mommy!

00:10.083 --> 00:13.583
LARK: Mommy!
GREG: I’m coming, Lark.

00:13.583 --> 00:14.667
Mommy?

00:14.667 --> 00:16.959
Good morning, Lark.

00:16.959 --> 00:19.500
What seems to be the problem?

00:19.500 --> 00:22.375
Oh, don’t worry, Daddy’s here.

00:22.375 --> 00:23.291
No Mommy?

00:23.291 --> 00:24.959
No, it’s Da-Da,
I know it’s confusing,

00:24.959 --> 00:28.917
-we wear the same pajamas.
-No Daddy, Mommy!

00:28.917 --> 00:31.250
What, but Da-Da loves you!

00:31.250 --> 00:32.500
Okay?

00:32.500 --> 00:33.875
Mommy!

00:33.875 --> 00:35.208
Hey,

00:35.208 --> 00:37.458
Da-Da, Da-Da.

00:37.458 --> 00:40.000
Hey, look at me in the eyes.

00:40.000 --> 00:43.166
Da-Da loves you.

00:43.166 --> 00:45.208
Mommy.

00:45.208 --> 00:48.917
♪

00:48.917 --> 00:51.792
GREG: I mean, I can’t believe
she rejected me like that.

00:51.792 --> 00:52.750
I mean, I’m her dad

00:52.750 --> 00:54.500
not a LinkedIn request.

00:54.500 --> 00:56.458
No Daddy, Mommy!

00:56.458 --> 00:57.709
No, Lark!

00:57.709 --> 01:00.000
Huh, see? Doesn’t feel
so good, does it?

01:00.000 --> 01:03.709
-Greg, honestly!
-What, she started it.

01:03.709 --> 01:05.583
I got no beef with her,
I’m just giving her a taste

01:05.583 --> 01:06.917
of her own medicine,
that’s all.

01:06.917 --> 01:08.083
She’s a baby!

01:08.083 --> 01:09.917
She doesn’t even know
what medicine is!

01:09.917 --> 01:11.333
I’m pretty sure
she thinks we die

01:11.333 --> 01:12.333
when we leave the room.

01:12.333 --> 01:15.583
Yeah, well, she hurt
my feelings, and look at her!

01:15.583 --> 01:17.500
She doesn’t even
look like she’s sorry.

01:17.500 --> 01:18.542
Shh.

01:18.542 --> 01:19.792
Don’t shush me.

01:19.792 --> 01:21.959
JEN: Honey, look,
it’s just a phase.

01:21.959 --> 01:24.083
Really, I mean,
this week she wants me,

01:24.083 --> 01:26.291
next week she’ll want you.

01:26.291 --> 01:28.250
-You really think so?
-Of course!

01:28.250 --> 01:30.041
Although we can’t really know
unless we get divorced

01:30.041 --> 01:32.792
and she has to choose
who she wants to live with.

01:32.792 --> 01:33.667
Mommy!

01:36.250 --> 01:39.500
♪

01:39.500 --> 01:40.834
Look what Daddy brought!

01:40.834 --> 01:43.542
Lark’s favorite, strawberries!

01:43.542 --> 01:45.625
No, Mommy.

01:45.625 --> 01:48.917
What do you want her for,
she’s not that great.

01:48.917 --> 01:50.333
Hey, there you are,
will you tell your daughter

01:50.333 --> 01:51.959
you’re not that great?

01:51.959 --> 01:55.000
Are you wearing my perfume?

01:55.000 --> 01:56.000
It was next to my cologne,

01:56.000 --> 01:57.417
and I accidentally grabbed it

01:57.417 --> 01:59.875
-and spilled some on myself.
-Uh-huh.

01:59.875 --> 02:00.709
Did my, uh,

02:00.709 --> 02:03.875
necklace spill on ya too?

02:03.875 --> 02:05.458
I thought those
were my dog tags.

02:05.458 --> 02:06.750
Oh, my God, Greg.

02:06.750 --> 02:08.542
You can’t make
Lark like you more

02:08.542 --> 02:10.166
by making her think you’re me.

02:10.166 --> 02:12.750
She loves you!

02:12.750 --> 02:15.667
Also, um, I’m gonna need you
to get me a new perfume.

02:15.667 --> 02:17.917
You’ve ruined that one for me.

02:17.917 --> 02:20.834
Okay.

02:20.834 --> 02:22.500
Bye, Lark!

02:22.500 --> 02:24.000
Daddy loves you!

02:24.000 --> 02:26.250
LARK: No!

02:26.250 --> 02:27.583
JOHN: You know what
would have happened

02:27.583 --> 02:29.125
if you’d have
pulled that crap on me

02:29.125 --> 02:30.250
when you were a baby, hm?

02:30.250 --> 02:31.458
-What?
-Hm?

02:31.458 --> 02:32.458
Ow!

02:32.458 --> 02:34.750
Well, you asked.

02:34.750 --> 02:37.000
Here’s some advice.

02:37.000 --> 02:39.667
Chicks like you more
if you ignore them, huh.

02:39.667 --> 02:40.917
Lark’s no different.

02:40.917 --> 02:43.041
If you wanna win her back,
just make her jealous.

02:43.041 --> 02:44.333
Dad, I’m not dating my daughter.

02:44.333 --> 02:46.375
I’m not gonna play mind games...

02:46.375 --> 02:48.125
except for peek-a-boo.

02:48.125 --> 02:50.208
Trust me.

02:50.208 --> 02:52.375
She’ll come crawlin’ back to ya,

02:52.375 --> 02:54.417
literally.

02:54.417 --> 02:56.250
Lark’s walking now, Dad.

02:56.250 --> 02:57.166
She is?

02:57.166 --> 02:59.166
♪

02:59.166 --> 03:01.667
Look at this, I’m pushin’ you!

03:01.667 --> 03:04.917
We are havin’ such a good time!

03:04.917 --> 03:06.208
Lark, are you lookin’ at this?

03:06.208 --> 03:07.417
Huh?

03:07.417 --> 03:08.667
This could be you,

03:08.667 --> 03:10.250
but you playin’.

03:10.250 --> 03:11.875
Yeah, look at that.

03:11.875 --> 03:13.458
WOMAN: You have to stop
pushin’ my kid.

03:13.458 --> 03:14.875
-What?
-I thought I was going to be

03:14.875 --> 03:16.792
okay with this,
but it’s just weird.

03:16.792 --> 03:18.208
No, it’s not weird.

03:18.208 --> 03:20.250
I mean, I’m just trying
to make my daughter jealous.

03:20.250 --> 03:21.291
Okay.

03:23.959 --> 03:26.542
Thanks anyways.

03:26.542 --> 03:28.500
Wow, Lark.

03:28.500 --> 03:30.917
Gosh, that must be difficult.

03:30.917 --> 03:32.375
I am really sorry

03:32.375 --> 03:33.667
that you had to see me

03:33.667 --> 03:36.333
and my new bestie
have so much fun.

03:36.333 --> 03:39.125
Yeah, I mean, if you want
I could give you a push.

03:39.125 --> 03:40.667
I mean, doesn’t
matter to me either way.

03:40.667 --> 03:41.834
No!

03:44.083 --> 03:45.959
It’s the only word she knows.

03:45.959 --> 03:47.917
LARK: Potato.

03:47.917 --> 03:50.917
"No" and "potato."

03:50.917 --> 03:52.917
Mother is Russian.

03:52.917 --> 03:55.375
♪

03:55.375 --> 03:56.750
Okay, Lark,

03:56.750 --> 03:58.834
time for a little lesson
in supply and demand.

04:01.959 --> 04:04.417
You want this candy,

04:04.417 --> 04:07.542
and I want your
love and affection.

04:07.542 --> 04:10.625
So, let’s make a deal.

04:10.625 --> 04:12.000
Huh, okay?

04:12.000 --> 04:14.458
No!

04:14.458 --> 04:15.834
Lark’s not responding to

04:15.834 --> 04:17.250
just straight-up bribery?

04:17.250 --> 04:19.583
No, no, what if
this lasts forever?

04:19.583 --> 04:20.625
I mean, some phases don’t end.

04:20.625 --> 04:23.041
I mean, look at Harrison Ford
and that stupid earring.

04:23.041 --> 04:24.458
Everything runs its course.

04:24.458 --> 04:25.917
Remember, there was
a time when you thought

04:25.917 --> 04:27.125
everything was both

04:27.125 --> 04:30.750
-dope and bomb-diggity?
-No doubt.

04:30.750 --> 04:34.000
-Mm-hmm.
LARK: Up, Daddy, up!

04:34.000 --> 04:35.375
Did you hear that?

04:35.375 --> 04:36.959
Up, Daddy!

04:36.959 --> 04:39.750
-Whoa, look at that!
-Yeah?

04:39.750 --> 04:42.417
-Yeah!
GREG: Come here!

04:42.417 --> 04:45.000
Come here, oh, you’re back.

04:45.000 --> 04:46.959
We’re back, baby!

04:46.959 --> 04:49.250
We’re back,
I knew you’d come around.

04:49.250 --> 04:52.166
I knew it was only
a matter of time.

04:52.166 --> 04:53.125
You wanna know what?

04:53.125 --> 04:55.083
I wanna take her to
the Sears Portrait gallery

04:55.083 --> 04:56.583
before she starts
hating me again.

04:56.583 --> 04:57.875
-Okay, yeah.
-So, will you just take her?

04:57.875 --> 04:58.792
I’m gonna go get our matching

04:58.792 --> 04:59.875
-overalls.
-Come here, baby.

04:59.875 --> 05:02.083
GREG: Yeah.
JEN: Okay.

05:02.083 --> 05:05.291
GREG: Be right back!
-All right.

05:05.291 --> 05:07.375
Thanks, Larkie,
that was amazing acting.

05:07.375 --> 05:09.792
The thing is that most daddies
are just very sensitive,

05:09.792 --> 05:11.583
you know, because they haven’t
gone through nine months

05:11.583 --> 05:14.208
of a living hellscape
to give birth to you.

05:14.208 --> 05:15.709
Anyway, we’re back.

05:15.709 --> 05:16.625
(laughing)

05:16.625 --> 05:18.834
No, Mommy, Daddy!

05:18.834 --> 05:20.041
What?

05:20.041 --> 05:21.166
Daddy!

05:21.166 --> 05:22.333
No, no,

05:22.333 --> 05:24.166
Momma loves you.

05:24.166 --> 05:26.417
Oh, no, oh God, no!

05:26.417 --> 05:28.834
(crying)

05:32.041 --> 05:33.917
I know!

05:33.917 --> 05:35.917
♪

05:35.917 --> 05:37.500
Oh, I’m so excited
to try this place.

05:37.500 --> 05:39.667
I hear they have a bunch
of healthy options.

05:39.667 --> 05:41.333
Oh, just what I love,

05:41.333 --> 05:42.375
healthy options.

05:45.542 --> 05:47.458
Okay, what is up
with the lighting in here?

05:47.458 --> 05:48.625
I mean, yeah,
it makes you look like

05:48.625 --> 05:49.959
a young Henry Kissinger,

05:49.959 --> 05:52.792
but it’s terrible
for reading the menu.

05:52.792 --> 05:55.125
Sure it’s the lighting?

05:55.125 --> 05:56.166
What’s that supposed to mean?

05:56.166 --> 05:58.625
Well, you’re makin’
the British face.

05:58.625 --> 06:00.667
-What?
-People only look like this

06:00.667 --> 06:02.375
when they either need glasses,

06:02.375 --> 06:04.834
or they’re British.

06:04.834 --> 06:06.041
Glasses?

06:06.041 --> 06:07.125
Oh, come on, babe.

06:07.125 --> 06:08.917
Nothin’ goes wrong
on this body, okay?

06:08.917 --> 06:10.750
I had two of our babies
standing up.

06:10.750 --> 06:13.542
Oh, well since
you can see, then...

06:13.542 --> 06:14.625
I was thinkin’
about gettin’ this.

06:14.625 --> 06:15.750
You think that’s
healthy enough?

06:15.750 --> 06:17.333
You see it,
right where my finger is?

06:17.333 --> 06:18.250
Yeah, uh-huh.

06:18.250 --> 06:19.583
-You can see that.
-Yeah, no, no, I see it.

06:19.583 --> 06:20.583
I can see it.

06:20.583 --> 06:21.792
Oh.

06:21.792 --> 06:23.166
Well, then that’s what I’ll get.

06:23.166 --> 06:24.083
Yummy.

06:24.083 --> 06:26.917
♪

06:26.917 --> 06:29.834
WAITER: No one’s wife has ever
let them order this before.

06:29.834 --> 06:31.834
Well, no one has
a wife like mine!

06:31.834 --> 06:33.917
(sparklers crackling)

06:33.917 --> 06:36.375
I’m so happy that you’re happy!

06:36.375 --> 06:39.041
Wait ’till you see
what I ordered for dessert.

06:39.041 --> 06:42.166
♪

06:42.166 --> 06:44.291
Mom, that’s not milk.

06:44.291 --> 06:46.959
That’s egg whites.

06:46.959 --> 06:48.667
Yeah, yeah I know that.

06:48.667 --> 06:50.208
It’s got extra protein.

06:50.208 --> 06:52.458
You don’t wanna stay
this height forever, huh?

06:52.458 --> 06:54.709
Yeah, you too, right?

06:54.709 --> 06:57.041
-All organic, okay.
-That’s okay.

06:57.041 --> 07:00.083
I’ll just drink this
wine cooler you gave me

07:00.083 --> 07:01.291
instead of juice.

07:01.291 --> 07:02.834
CLEMENTINE: Hey, you got peach?

07:02.834 --> 07:03.750
Can we trade?

07:03.750 --> 07:04.959
What’s wrong with Mom?

07:04.959 --> 07:06.834
She’s in denial about
losin’ her eyesight,

07:06.834 --> 07:08.500
but don’t take advantage of it

07:08.500 --> 07:11.041
’cause that’s what I’m doin’,
and we can’t all do it.

07:11.041 --> 07:11.959
Better go make sure she’s not

07:11.959 --> 07:14.709
brushin’ her teeth
with my butt cream again.

07:14.709 --> 07:16.000
You guys thinkin’
what I’m thinkin’?

07:16.000 --> 07:19.792
♪

07:19.792 --> 07:22.000
Hey, Mom, I just
texted you a question.

07:22.000 --> 07:24.000
Yeah?

07:24.000 --> 07:24.917
Okay.

07:24.917 --> 07:26.750
Um, wow.

07:26.750 --> 07:28.667
-Well, that’s a--
-That’s a yes?

07:28.667 --> 07:29.583
-Yes, yes!
-Cool.

07:29.583 --> 07:30.667
Come on, that’s a yes.

07:30.667 --> 07:32.709
Somebody needs to go get
his ears checked.

07:32.709 --> 07:34.375
Go, go!

07:36.417 --> 07:40.417
Hey, Mom, could you
please sign this for me?

07:40.417 --> 07:42.417
You know what, I’m gonna
need you to read that to me

07:42.417 --> 07:43.583
’cause I’m a little bit drunk.

07:43.583 --> 07:47.959
♪

07:47.959 --> 07:49.917
Heather, did you sign a form
saying Samantha could be

07:49.917 --> 07:53.291
an exchange student
in Barcelona?

07:53.291 --> 07:54.250
What, no!

07:54.250 --> 07:55.375
Yes, you did!

07:55.375 --> 07:57.291
She’s gonna be there all summer,
and we’re gonna be marooned here

07:57.291 --> 07:59.000
with some kid named Alvero,

07:59.000 --> 08:00.959
who’s gonna wonder why
our house smells so awful

08:00.959 --> 08:03.333
because you also said Tyler
could empty his septic tank

08:03.333 --> 08:04.417
into our backyard.

08:04.417 --> 08:05.959
What?

08:05.959 --> 08:08.000
Look, it is time
you get some glasses!

08:08.000 --> 08:09.458
Oh, honey, no, please, stop.

08:09.458 --> 08:10.500
Can we talk about this later?

08:10.500 --> 08:13.542
I took some aspirin
for my headache,

08:13.542 --> 08:16.250
and my stomach is
feeling very squirrely.

08:16.250 --> 08:18.667
Well, good news is
you won’t have worms anymore,

08:18.667 --> 08:21.917
but the bad news is you might
experience excessive panting.

08:21.917 --> 08:23.333
-What?
-Ya took Lucky’s

08:23.333 --> 08:24.500
heartworm medicine.

08:28.625 --> 08:30.083
Okay, why do we still have this?

08:30.083 --> 08:32.458
Lucky’s been dead
for five years!

08:32.458 --> 08:34.792
The real question here
is why won’t you get glasses?

08:34.792 --> 08:36.375
You can’t see!

08:36.375 --> 08:41.000
♪

08:41.000 --> 08:43.250
Hey, hey, you look hot,

08:43.250 --> 08:45.959
like Miss Chalone,
my middle school librarian.

08:45.959 --> 08:47.625
I know, I look old and gross

08:47.625 --> 08:50.125
like my middle school librarian,
who used to keep

08:50.125 --> 08:53.125
pencils in her unibrow.

08:53.125 --> 08:54.208
I know these milestones

08:54.208 --> 08:56.041
-can be a bummer.
-Oh, they suck.

08:56.041 --> 08:57.291
But no matter how old you get,

08:57.291 --> 08:59.667
we are getting there together.

08:59.667 --> 09:01.542
And I am always gonna
think of you as that girl

09:01.542 --> 09:03.291
who convinced me that
you can’t get pregnant

09:03.291 --> 09:05.583
the first time you have sex.

09:05.583 --> 09:07.375
I did, yeah.

09:07.375 --> 09:09.625
Now why don’t you yell at me
for spilling fruit juice

09:09.625 --> 09:11.917
-in my library book.
-Oh!

09:11.917 --> 09:15.417
Well, I am going to go get
something for us to spill...

09:15.417 --> 09:18.375
and a ruler
to spank you with.

09:18.375 --> 09:20.166
♪

09:20.166 --> 09:22.083
I am so glad
my mom went to sleep

09:22.083 --> 09:25.083
instead of trying
to hang out with us.

09:25.083 --> 09:26.083
HEATHER: Hey, guys!

09:26.083 --> 09:27.250
What’s up?

09:30.333 --> 09:31.417
Oh, my God, Jenna.

09:34.000 --> 09:36.291
Look, the same!

09:36.291 --> 09:37.959
We’re twinsies!

09:37.959 --> 09:39.709
That’s so cool, Mrs. Hughes.

09:39.709 --> 09:43.125
-Glasses buddies.
-Yeah, on fleek!

09:43.125 --> 09:44.583
(explosion sound effect)

09:44.583 --> 09:46.875
I’m gonna go drink my drink.

09:46.875 --> 09:49.667
HEATHER: Awesome!

09:49.667 --> 09:51.041
Oh, my God.

09:51.041 --> 09:53.333
I can’t believe I was
wearing old lady glasses.

09:53.333 --> 09:56.625
♪

09:56.625 --> 09:58.667
MATT: Anyway, it is such a,
such a pleasure to meet you.

09:58.667 --> 09:59.917
I’m a big art of your fan.

09:59.917 --> 10:01.750
That’s a--big fart--

10:01.750 --> 10:03.959
-He’s saying he’s a big fan.
-I got that.

10:06.083 --> 10:09.250
♪

10:09.250 --> 10:10.625
MATT: Don’t worry,
we’re not gonna be late.

10:10.625 --> 10:12.250
Your father said his
boat docks at six bells,

10:12.250 --> 10:13.333
which is either in 20 minutes,

10:13.333 --> 10:14.917
or well, you know, yesterday.

10:14.917 --> 10:16.500
So, we actually may be late.

10:16.500 --> 10:18.208
Well, then walk faster!

10:18.208 --> 10:20.041
I just don’t want him
to have any reason to say no

10:20.041 --> 10:21.792
when you ask for his
blessing to marry me.

10:21.792 --> 10:22.709
Just, I’m his favorite,

10:22.709 --> 10:24.458
and I only get to see him
a couple times a year.

10:24.458 --> 10:26.166
I just want this
to go perfectly.

10:26.166 --> 10:27.917
I promise that it will.

10:27.917 --> 10:29.542
Is that the voice
you’re gonna use?

10:29.542 --> 10:31.250
You mean my voice?

10:31.250 --> 10:33.166
Sorry, it must be
the acoustics out here.

10:33.166 --> 10:34.291
Look, if it makes you
feel any better,

10:34.291 --> 10:35.333
I’m nervous too, okay?

10:35.333 --> 10:36.375
He’s an amazing artist.

10:36.375 --> 10:39.291
His mural at the Sonoma
airport blew my mind.

10:39.291 --> 10:40.917
A triangle sitting
on top of a sphere,

10:40.917 --> 10:42.792
I mean, that broke
all the rules.

10:42.792 --> 10:44.083
Well, that’s kind of his thing.

10:44.083 --> 10:46.250
That, and having a bunch
of kids with a bunch of women,

10:46.250 --> 10:48.792
and dodging his taxes
living at sea.

10:48.792 --> 10:49.750
Got a lot of things.

10:49.750 --> 10:52.458
Well, that’s another
one of his things.

10:52.458 --> 10:53.834
Oh, Daddy!

10:53.834 --> 10:55.583
There’s my favorite!

10:55.583 --> 10:56.875
(laughing)

10:56.875 --> 10:58.834
Well, I’m the only one
that still talks to you.

10:58.834 --> 11:01.792
Well, that’s why
you’re my favorite.

11:01.792 --> 11:03.875
-You must be Matt.
-Hey!

11:03.875 --> 11:06.583
(laughing)

11:06.583 --> 11:07.667
Why am I laughing?

11:07.667 --> 11:08.667
I don’t know why I’m laughing.

11:08.667 --> 11:10.125
Nobody even said
anything funny anyway.

11:10.125 --> 11:12.208
-Cool boat!
-Oh, well, thanks!

11:12.208 --> 11:15.417
-This is, uh, my wife, Sangria.
MATT: Oh, hey!

11:15.417 --> 11:16.625
SANGRIA: Oh, hi!

11:16.625 --> 11:17.750
-Hi.
SANGRIA: Nice to meet you.

11:17.750 --> 11:18.875
MATT: Nice to meet you too.

11:18.875 --> 11:20.750
-This is a gift for you guys.
-Uh, this is the book that

11:20.750 --> 11:21.917
Colleen and I created together.

11:21.917 --> 11:23.291
I did the illustrations.

11:23.291 --> 11:25.542
This brings me great happiness

11:25.542 --> 11:28.208
-that Colleen is with an artist.
MATT: Oh.

11:28.208 --> 11:31.083
Her Daddy issues
finally paid off.

11:31.083 --> 11:33.291
Um, anyway, it’s really
nice to meet you.

11:33.291 --> 11:34.875
I’m a huge fan of your art.

11:34.875 --> 11:36.542
Well, come, let me show you

11:36.542 --> 11:38.125
-my latest piece.
-Really?

11:38.125 --> 11:40.250
Can I--Okay, sorry.

11:40.250 --> 11:41.917
So, are you happy?

11:41.917 --> 11:45.083
Oh, yeah, your dad is
so random, I’m obsessed.

11:45.083 --> 11:46.709
Yeah, you said that
in your Christmas letter.

11:46.709 --> 11:48.458
♪

11:48.458 --> 11:51.000
MIGUEL: So, what do you think?

11:51.000 --> 11:53.333
This is my latest piece.

11:53.333 --> 11:55.583
I think when it’s finished
it’s gonna be great.

11:55.583 --> 11:56.875
It’s already done.

11:56.875 --> 12:00.667
The Bellagio has these in
all of their handicap stalls.

12:00.667 --> 12:03.041
Well, this seems about
as good a time as any to, um,

12:03.041 --> 12:04.500
to ask you a very
important question.

12:04.500 --> 12:06.166
Thirty bucks, without the frame.

12:06.166 --> 12:07.291
Mm, no.

12:07.291 --> 12:08.709
Um, sir,

12:08.709 --> 12:12.208
I’m here because I’m
in love with your daughter,

12:12.208 --> 12:14.208
and I would like to
ask for your blessing

12:14.208 --> 12:16.125
to get married.

12:16.125 --> 12:18.291
I really like you, Matt.

12:18.291 --> 12:19.625
You know,
when I look in your eyes,

12:19.625 --> 12:21.917
I see the soul of an artist,

12:21.917 --> 12:23.458
which is why this is
the easiest thing

12:23.458 --> 12:27.125
in the world for me to say, no!

12:27.125 --> 12:29.208
Is that Spanish for yes?

12:29.208 --> 12:30.959
No, that’s Spanish for no.

12:30.959 --> 12:31.917
Is it my voice?

12:31.917 --> 12:33.458
Because I can talk like this.

12:33.458 --> 12:35.500
No, no, it’s not your voice, no.

12:35.500 --> 12:37.834
It’s your potential
as an artist.

12:37.834 --> 12:40.417
Colleen says you’re
an incredible talent,

12:40.417 --> 12:41.667
but all that would go to waste

12:41.667 --> 12:44.667
if you shackle yourself
to one woman.

12:44.667 --> 12:46.625
An artist needs to be as free

12:46.625 --> 12:48.083
-as his brushstrokes.
-Right,

12:48.083 --> 12:49.792
but you’re married to paella.

12:49.792 --> 12:51.750
Sangria.

12:51.750 --> 12:53.458
Maybe you have a point.

12:53.458 --> 12:55.792
Maybe that’s why
my career’s in the toilet.

12:55.792 --> 12:57.583
Well, no, it’s not
in the toilet,

12:57.583 --> 12:59.083
but it’s in a place where
you can definitely see it

12:59.083 --> 13:00.625
when you’re sitting
on the toilet.

13:00.625 --> 13:02.166
What, what, uh,
what’s happening?

13:02.166 --> 13:03.291
Mr. Ortega?

13:03.291 --> 13:06.000
Thank you,
you’ve opened my eyes.

13:06.000 --> 13:09.041
Oh, um, um...

13:09.041 --> 13:11.250
Where are you going, Mr. Ortega?

13:11.250 --> 13:13.291
Oh, no, no, no, no,
what are you doin’?

13:13.291 --> 13:14.417
(splashing)

13:14.417 --> 13:16.208
-I didn’t mean for you to--
-No, you did!

13:16.208 --> 13:18.125
It took another artist
with the voice of a donkey

13:18.125 --> 13:20.375
to make me see
what a sellout I’ve become.

13:20.375 --> 13:22.166
Sangria!

13:22.166 --> 13:24.250
-It’s over!
SANGRIA: Over?

13:24.250 --> 13:26.041
What movie were you watching?

13:26.041 --> 13:28.667
Our marriage is over!

13:28.667 --> 13:30.834
Oh, I haven’t seen that one.

13:30.834 --> 13:31.834
What?

13:31.834 --> 13:32.917
♪

13:32.917 --> 13:34.458
(crying)

13:34.458 --> 13:35.375
How dare you!

13:35.375 --> 13:36.709
Get outta my way!

13:39.333 --> 13:40.500
Take that!

13:40.500 --> 13:42.000
(crying)

13:42.000 --> 13:45.542
I’m already inspired.

13:45.542 --> 13:47.709
What just happened?

13:47.709 --> 13:49.000
Well, it’s complicated, Colleen.

13:49.000 --> 13:51.417
See, artists like
your father and I are

13:51.417 --> 13:53.208
-deep and passionate people--
-Uh-huh, did you get

13:53.208 --> 13:54.834
-the blessing or not?
-Um.

13:54.834 --> 13:56.083
It’s a simple question,
yes or no.

13:56.083 --> 13:57.625
It’s not as simple
as you would think.

14:01.083 --> 14:03.667
(water lapping)

14:03.667 --> 14:05.125
Why aren’t you using words?

14:05.125 --> 14:06.542
-It requires--
MIGUEL: Matt,

14:06.542 --> 14:07.542
I’ve changed my mind.

14:07.542 --> 14:08.875
-You have my blessing.
-Oh, thank God,

14:08.875 --> 14:10.583
-I was getting nervous.
MATT: Oh!

14:10.583 --> 14:11.542
Uh, what?

14:11.542 --> 14:13.959
I looked at your work,
and I realized that

14:13.959 --> 14:16.750
the greatest accomplishment
you will ever have in your life

14:16.750 --> 14:17.792
is marrying my daughter.

14:17.792 --> 14:21.166
-Aw!
-Oh, no, no, no, no.

14:21.166 --> 14:23.083
This is not an accurate
representation

14:23.083 --> 14:24.250
of my artistic vision, no.

14:24.250 --> 14:26.166
-I have a whole portfolio--
-Oh, that’s okay.

14:26.166 --> 14:27.500
-I get the gist.
-No, I don’t think

14:27.500 --> 14:28.583
-that ya do.
-Matt, what are you doing?

14:28.583 --> 14:29.750
-He gave us his blessing!
-Yeah,

14:29.750 --> 14:31.458
I don’t want his blessing.

14:31.458 --> 14:32.625
You should be happily married.

14:32.625 --> 14:34.250
No, I’ll never love again,

14:34.250 --> 14:36.500
but you will be so happy.

14:36.500 --> 14:39.917
Much like your crudely-drawn
chicken with teeth.

14:39.917 --> 14:41.208
-Good luck with this guy.
-Okay.

14:43.208 --> 14:44.417
Yay!

14:44.417 --> 14:45.500
Aren’t we blessed?

14:45.500 --> 14:47.917
♪

14:47.917 --> 14:50.875
MIKEY: Sorry I ruined your
photo of Laurel and Hardy.

14:50.875 --> 14:52.834
Those were my parents.

14:52.834 --> 14:54.125
No way!

14:54.125 --> 14:54.917
Lucky!

14:57.250 --> 15:00.917
♪

15:00.917 --> 15:02.083
MIKEY: Aunt Joan,

15:02.083 --> 15:03.500
what if I never
find love again?

15:03.500 --> 15:05.500
I can’t be alone forever.

15:05.500 --> 15:07.375
I just bought a ping-pong table.

15:07.375 --> 15:10.375
No, I promised my sister
I’d look after you.

15:10.375 --> 15:11.959
John and I are here for you.

15:11.959 --> 15:14.291
JOHN: Oh, to make
things very clear,

15:14.291 --> 15:16.834
I am not the one related to you.

15:16.834 --> 15:18.750
I can’t believe
Kelly did this to me.

15:18.750 --> 15:20.333
I mean, I stood by her,

15:20.333 --> 15:22.291
you know,
during the car accident,

15:22.291 --> 15:26.083
the dog attack,
both sex changes.

15:26.083 --> 15:29.291
The minute she lost
ten pounds, she dumped me.

15:29.291 --> 15:32.583
I lose ten pounds
when I go to the bathroom.

15:32.583 --> 15:33.917
I gotta go to the bathroom.

15:36.709 --> 15:39.125
God, how long is he
gonna stay with us?

15:39.125 --> 15:41.041
-Oh.
-If there’s a suicide

15:41.041 --> 15:43.458
in this house,
it hurts our resale.

15:43.458 --> 15:45.500
I have the perfect girl for him,

15:45.500 --> 15:47.208
Candice at the coffee shop.

15:47.208 --> 15:49.041
She’s sweet, and she’s kind,

15:49.041 --> 15:50.500
and she’s pretty!

15:50.500 --> 15:52.125
How are her standards?

15:52.125 --> 15:53.375
Low!

15:53.375 --> 15:54.542
Oh!

15:54.542 --> 15:57.083
I just know
that Mikey and Candice

15:57.083 --> 15:58.709
would be a perfect match.

15:58.709 --> 16:00.250
You know, all I have to do is

16:00.250 --> 16:02.792
change his
appearance completely,

16:02.792 --> 16:04.583
and ply them with alcohol.

16:04.583 --> 16:06.125
I hear wedding bells!

16:06.125 --> 16:07.667
♪

16:07.667 --> 16:10.000
GITTEL: So what are
we doing today

16:10.000 --> 16:11.959
with this big teddy bear?

16:11.959 --> 16:14.500
Just spiff him up so we can
meet at the coffee shop

16:14.500 --> 16:16.625
for coffee and coffee cake

16:16.625 --> 16:19.750
that we can chew
with our mouths closed.

16:19.750 --> 16:21.667
♪

16:21.667 --> 16:24.458
I wish I was coffee cake.

16:24.458 --> 16:27.583
You look like you could
pick me up without grunting.

16:27.583 --> 16:30.166
Oh, one of the discs
in my back’s leakin’ fluid.

16:30.166 --> 16:32.500
Oh, honey, I’m leaking
things from everywhere.

16:32.500 --> 16:35.166
Oh, well I’m glad
I’m wearin’ a smock.

16:35.166 --> 16:37.291
(laughing)

16:37.291 --> 16:41.834
♪

16:41.834 --> 16:43.208
Wow, so he can really cook

16:43.208 --> 16:45.083
-a whole pig?
-Yes!

16:45.083 --> 16:48.291
Yes, and he can do
other things too!

16:48.291 --> 16:50.291
I can’t think of them
at the moment,

16:50.291 --> 16:52.166
but, uh, he...

16:52.166 --> 16:53.875
can cook a whole pig!

16:53.875 --> 16:56.709
I’m gonna go check and make sure
that my eyebrows still match.

16:56.709 --> 16:58.083
Oh, it’s okay!

16:58.083 --> 17:00.542
He, he would probably
like that they don’t.

17:00.542 --> 17:02.458
Uh, hey, Aunt Joan.

17:02.458 --> 17:04.625
Uh, I’m a new man.

17:04.625 --> 17:06.583
My new man!

17:06.583 --> 17:08.667
Uh, Gittel’s gonna join us
for coffee if that’s all right.

17:08.667 --> 17:09.583
No.

17:09.583 --> 17:12.834
I’d like to order one pound.

17:12.834 --> 17:13.834
No!

17:13.834 --> 17:14.834
Doh!

17:14.834 --> 17:16.291
Mm, I actually have to run.

17:16.291 --> 17:18.458
My nephew’s
bar mitzvah is tonight...

17:18.458 --> 17:19.834
unless you wanna join me.

17:19.834 --> 17:21.041
The theme is "Joshua Rocks,"

17:21.041 --> 17:22.458
and there’s a guitar cake.

17:22.458 --> 17:23.709
That’s my favorite
kind of cake, Aunt Joan,

17:23.709 --> 17:25.959
do you mind if I go rage
at the bar mitzvah?

17:25.959 --> 17:27.291
-Fine.
-Yeah?

17:27.291 --> 17:29.917
Fine, go!

17:29.917 --> 17:30.834
Is he here?

17:30.834 --> 17:32.542
I just broke up
with my boyfriend.

17:32.542 --> 17:34.166
Didn’t I tell you?

17:34.166 --> 17:35.917
He couldn’t come!

17:35.917 --> 17:38.208
♪

17:38.208 --> 17:40.625
(moaning)

17:43.417 --> 17:45.750
Maybe I should
stay over tonight.

17:45.750 --> 17:46.959
Does this pull out?

17:46.959 --> 17:48.875
Uh, it does if I time it right.

17:48.875 --> 17:51.500
(laughing)

17:51.500 --> 17:52.417
We should go.

17:52.417 --> 17:55.250
I think us watching
is part of it.

17:55.250 --> 17:56.542
Oh.

17:58.417 --> 18:00.917
Who knew the most
annoying person in my life

18:00.917 --> 18:04.500
would fall for the most
annoying person in my family?

18:04.500 --> 18:07.875
They’re doing things
down there, Joanie.

18:07.875 --> 18:11.208
Now I see why your sister
wrapped her couch in plastic.

18:11.208 --> 18:12.041
Oh, please.

18:14.667 --> 18:15.917
You having fun?

18:15.917 --> 18:16.917
No.

18:16.917 --> 18:18.917
We’re not having anything.

18:18.917 --> 18:20.458
I can’t sleep with
her because I can’t

18:20.458 --> 18:22.083
show her my downstairs nose.

18:22.083 --> 18:24.458
Well, you got a stub?

18:24.458 --> 18:25.750
All right, let’s see it.

18:25.750 --> 18:28.458
No, no, no, I--

18:28.458 --> 18:30.583
Oh, I told her I was Jewish.

18:30.583 --> 18:31.709
JOHN: Why?
-Because that’s

18:31.709 --> 18:32.959
a deal breaker for her.

18:32.959 --> 18:34.959
But the second she sees
that I’m not...

18:34.959 --> 18:39.667
circumcised, the only thing
broken is gonna be my heart!

18:39.667 --> 18:40.959
And that.

18:40.959 --> 18:42.625
I’m sorry, you had that

18:42.625 --> 18:44.041
backed up in the cloud, right?

18:44.041 --> 18:47.792
Mikey, you can’t be in
a relationship built on a lie.

18:50.917 --> 18:51.875
You know what, you’re right.

18:51.875 --> 18:53.166
I gotta go back
and talk to her.

18:53.166 --> 18:54.500
-Yeah.
-I mean, what we have

18:54.500 --> 18:57.250
is stronger than any
skin covering my penis.

18:57.250 --> 19:00.041
Why don’t you go say
that wonderful line to her.

19:00.041 --> 19:02.458
♪

19:02.458 --> 19:04.375
(screaming)

19:04.375 --> 19:05.875
(glass shattering)

19:05.875 --> 19:08.417
She dumped me!

19:08.417 --> 19:09.500
Damn it!

19:12.041 --> 19:13.458
JOAN: I know a barista

19:13.458 --> 19:15.458
who would take your penis as-is.

19:15.458 --> 19:17.917
No, forget it.

19:17.917 --> 19:21.041
I’m staying in this bed
for the rest of my life.

19:21.041 --> 19:24.041
Sorry I ruined your photo
of Laurel and Hardy.

19:24.041 --> 19:25.959
Those were my parents.

19:25.959 --> 19:27.166
Which one was your mom?

19:27.166 --> 19:29.667
The skinny one or the fat one?

19:29.667 --> 19:31.125
The one with the moustache.

19:31.125 --> 19:33.000
♪

19:36.000 --> 19:37.208
♪

19:37.208 --> 19:39.208
HEATHER: Hey!

19:39.208 --> 19:40.875
What do you think?

19:40.875 --> 19:42.875
Haven’t you always worn glasses?

19:42.875 --> 19:44.750
Oh, Greg, come on!

19:44.750 --> 19:46.625
No wonder Lark
prefers Jen to you.

19:46.625 --> 19:50.291
JOAN: Thank you
so much for coming, Candice.

19:50.291 --> 19:52.125
-Here, sit here, dear.
-Oh, thank you.

19:52.125 --> 19:54.625
And thank you for bringing
all these stirrers!

19:54.625 --> 19:55.917
Oh, sure.

19:55.917 --> 19:57.625
I am so excited to finally meet

19:57.625 --> 19:59.125
this nephew of yours.

19:59.125 --> 20:01.834
I’ve always wanted
to date a nephew.

20:01.834 --> 20:03.542
JOAN: Huh.
MIKEY: Aunt Joan!

20:03.542 --> 20:05.083
-Hey, Aunt Joan.
JOAN: No.

20:05.083 --> 20:06.166
Dude, you were so right.

20:06.166 --> 20:07.542
Gittel thought about it,

20:07.542 --> 20:09.041
and she took me back.

20:09.041 --> 20:10.417
GITTEL: After a talk
with Rabbi David,

20:10.417 --> 20:12.208
I realized I should
take what I can get

20:12.208 --> 20:13.792
while I still have some eggs.

20:13.792 --> 20:15.583
MIKEY: And I realized that
if we’re gonna make this work,

20:15.583 --> 20:16.709
I have to show you

20:16.709 --> 20:18.834
that I’m just as
committed to your faith

20:18.834 --> 20:20.083
as I am to you.

20:20.083 --> 20:22.041
So, uh, guys,
put down the quiche,

20:22.041 --> 20:23.542
pull up a chair

20:23.542 --> 20:26.375
because this guy
is gonna circumcise me.

20:26.375 --> 20:27.917
Oh, my God!

20:27.917 --> 20:29.875
RABBI DAVID: I thought
I was here to bless the food.

20:29.875 --> 20:31.834
Nope, you’re giving me
a downstairs nose job.

20:31.834 --> 20:33.458
Oh, I love these.

20:33.458 --> 20:34.667
I’ll get my bag.

20:34.667 --> 20:36.250
CANDICE: Should I go?

20:36.250 --> 20:38.458
No, dear, you stay.

20:38.458 --> 20:39.417
I’ll go.

20:39.417 --> 20:46.333
♪
